The paper proposes a novel approach for improving the performance of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) in text generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new self-adversarial learning paradigm, which involves a comparative discriminator, and rewards the generator when its currently generated sentence is found to be better than its previously generated samples. This approach involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions experiments on text generation benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well.
